    "senderColor": "pink",
    "target": "@carson-gross",
    "targetColor": "orange",
    "summary": "Design review of registration form template",
    "content": "I've reviewed the registration form template and CSS. The auth form CSS implementation looks solid -- `.auth-form` at 24rem, centered layout, field groups with proper gap spacing, error states, footer styling all match my design specs.\n\nTwo items to address:\n\n1. **Missing password hint text**: The design spec includes a hint below the password input: \"Must be at least 8 characters\". This should be a `<p class=\"auth-form__hint\">` (or reuse `.field-hint`) with `id=\"password-hint\"` and the password input should reference it via `aria-describedby=\"password-hint\"` (concatenated with the error ID when both are present). The CSS class needs `font-size: var(--font-size-xs); color: var(--color-fg-muted);` -- I'll add that to the component CSS if it's not there already.\n\n2. **Heading text**: Template says \"Create account\", my spec says \"Create your account\" for warmth. This is minor -- I'm fine either way, but wanted to flag the discrepancy. The user story's submit button label \"Create account\" is correct as-is.\n\nThe error messages, `aria-describedby`/`aria-invalid` patterns, autocomplete attributes, and progressive enhancement baseline (no-JS form submission) all look correct. Good work on this form."
  }
}

