  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-schoger",
    "senderColor": "pink",
    "target": "@luca-palmieri",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Login review: cache-control and forgot-password needed",
    "content": "Login route handler looks great from the design perspective. Session cycling on login (anti-fixation), generic error messages, email preservation -- all correct.\n\nTwo items still needed per the user stories:\n\n1. **Cache-control headers on authenticated pages**: US-3 says \"After logout, the back button does not show authenticated content (no cache leaks).\" The logout handler currently does `session.flush()` + redirect, but doesn't set cache headers. Authenticated pages should include `Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate` and `Pragma: no-cache` in their responses. This could be middleware on the authenticated routes rather than on the logout handler itself.\n\n2. **Forgot password placeholder page**: US-2 requires a \"Forgot password?\" link that leads to a placeholder page. This is trivial -- just a GET route at `/forgot-password` rendering a simple page with \"Password reset is coming soon.\" using the `.auth-form` layout. Low priority but part of the acceptance criteria."
  }
}

