Getting ahead on Task #7 design specs (View todo list + Add todo). This is the core page of the app.

## Todo List Page Layout

```html
{% extends "base.html" %}
{% block title %}My Todos -- Todo List{% endblock %}

{% block nav %}
<div class="site-header">
    <a href="/todos" class="site-header__brand">Todo List</a>
    <div class="site-header__actions">
        <span>{{ user_email }}</span>
        <form method="post" action="/logout">
            <button type="submit" class="button--text">Sign out</button>
        </form>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<h1>My Todos</h1>

<!-- Add todo form -- hero position at top -->
<form method="post" action="/todos" class="todo-add">
    <label for="new-todo" class="visually-hidden">New todo</label>
    <input
        type="text"
        id="new-todo"
        name="title"
        placeholder="What do you need to do?"
        maxlength="300"
        autocomplete="off"
        class="todo-add__input"
    >
    <button type="submit" class="todo-add__button">Add</button>
</form>

<!-- Todo list -->
{% if todos.is_empty() %}
<p class="todo-empty">No todos yet.</p>
{% else %}
<ul class="todo-list" role="list">
    {% for todo in todos %}
    <li class="todo-item {% if todo.completed %}todo-item--completed{% endif %}">
        <form method="post" action="/todos/{{ todo.id }}/toggle" class="todo-item__toggle">
            <button type="submit"
                class="todo-item__checkbox"
                aria-label="{% if todo.completed %}Mark '{{ todo.title }}' as pending{% else %}Mark '{{ todo.title }}' as complete{% endif %}">
                {% if todo.completed %}
                <svg aria-hidden="true"><!-- checkmark icon --></svg>
                {% endif %}
            </button>
        </form>
        <span class="todo-item__title">{{ todo.title }}</span>
        <!-- Edit and delete buttons come in Tasks #9 and #20 -->
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
</ul>
{% endif %}
{% endblock %}
```

## Component CSS

```css
/* ---- Todo Add Form ---- */
.todo-add {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--space-sm);
  margin-block: var(--space-lg);
}

.todo-add__input {
  flex: 1;
}

.todo-add__button {
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* ---- Todo List ---- */
.todo-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

.todo-item {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-sm);
  padding-block: var(--space-sm);
  padding-inline: var(--space-sm);
  border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

.todo-item:first-child {
  border-block-start: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

/* Completed items: strikethrough + muted color */
.todo-item--completed .todo-item__title {
  text-decoration: line-through;
  color: var(--color-fg-muted);
}

/* Checkbox button */
.todo-item__checkbox {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  inline-size: 1.25rem;
  block-size: 1.25rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  border: 2px solid var(--color-border-strong);
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  background: var(--color-bg-raised);
  color: white;
  padding: 0;
}

.todo-item--completed .todo-item__checkbox {
  background-color: var(--color-primary);
  border-color: var(--color-primary);
}

.todo-item__title {
  flex: 1;
  min-inline-size: 0; /* allow text truncation */
  overflow-wrap: break-word;
}

/* ---- Empty State ---- */
.todo-empty {
  color: var(--color-fg-muted);
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  text-align: center;
  padding-block: var(--space-xl);
}
```

Key design decisions:
- **Add form is the hero**: Big input at top, always visible. Label is visually hidden but present for screen readers. Placeholder guides the user.
- **"Add" button**: Small, beside the input. Not full-width -- it's secondary to the input itself.
- **Todo items**: Simple rows with left-aligned checkbox, title fills remaining space. Horizontal borders separate items.
- **Completed state**: Strikethrough text + muted color (two visual indicators, not just color). Checkbox fills with primary blue.
- **Empty state**: Centered, muted, small text. Brief -- "No todos yet." The add input above is obvious enough.
- **No pagination**: For MVP, all todos render at once. 100+ items will still be fast with server rendering.

